This paper deals with robotics and automation in logistics, which falls under the scope of the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of suction cups for pick-and-place tasks also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for object recognition and manipulation. The proposed model and procedures for contact stability and time-optimal path planning also involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) concepts.
